il"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 Tbsp lemon juice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"24 large raw prawns, peeled and deveined"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g onions, quartered"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 garlic cloves"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g cucumbers, unpeeled, cut in pieces"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 lemon, cut in round slices, then quartered"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 heaped tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g milk"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"40 g plain flour"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 Tbsp fresh dill, chopped (optional)"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","733 kJ \/ 175 kcal","12 g","10 g","9 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["If using frozen prawns, defrost before marinating.<br>- Unpeeled cucumbers give more colour and flavour to the soup.<br>- Long skewers can be cut to fit the Varoma dish.<br>- In hot weather this soup can be served chilled. For a fresh summer flavour, replace dill with fresh mint or coriander.","<i>Cucumber makes a really refreshing soup. For a creamy white soup, peel the cucumbers and for a pale green soup, leave the skin on. Either way is perfect when you have a bumper crop in the garden! The prawn skewers add a touch of elegance and complement the flavour of the soup.<\/i>","Instead of flour use <b>150 g cooked<b> potatoes, cut in pieces, to thicken the soup.<br>- Use cream instead of milk, or half cream, half milk.<br>- For vegetarian skewers, replace lemon slices with cherry tomatoes and prawns with one or several of the following: small mushrooms <b>(Ø 3 cm),<b> feta cheese cubes, or tofu cubes marinated in soy sauce.<br>- The soup can also be seasoned with a splash of dry white wine."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","35m","6 portions"]}